 Hunt, himself?   Jackson offers new and unorthodox accounts of the coming-to-fame of some of Britain's most revered authors and compares their reputations and afterlives with those of their contemporary rivals. What she discovers about trends, champions, institutional power, and writers' conscious efforts to position themselves for posterity casts fresh light on the actual processes that lead to literary fame.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAuthors and readersxHistoryx19th centuryxEngland. 0aAuthors and readerszEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 0aAuthors, EnglishxAppreciationx19th century. 0aAuthors, Englishy19th centuryxAppreciation. 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aEnglish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aFamexHistoryx19th century. 0aFamexHistoryy19th century. 0aInfluence (Literary, artistic, etc.)xHistoryx19th century. 0aInfluence (Literary, artistic, etc.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aReputationxHistoryx19th centuryxEngland. 0aReputationzEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 0aRomanticismxHistoryx19th centuryxEngland. 0aRomanticismzEnglandxHistoryy19th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Gothic & Romance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213300423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300213300.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles